<i>noun</i>: 하직 [하ː직], 하야 [하ː야], 퇴위 [퇴ː위/퉤ː위], 퇴사 [퇴ː사/퉤ː사], 퇴거 [퇴ː거/퉤ː거], 체념 [체념], 사표 [사표], 사퇴 [사퇴/사퉤], 사직서 [사직써], 사직 [사직], 사임 [사임] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>하직 [하ː직]</dt><br>
<dd>1. farewell; good-bye</dd><br>
<dd>먼 길을 떠날 때 웃어른께 작별을 고하는 인사.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of bidding farewell to elders when one is about to take a long journey.</dd><br>
<dd>2. ending; quitting; resignation</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 마지막으로 하거나 그만둠.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of doing something for the last time, or quitting it.</dd><br>
<dd>3. passing away; parting; leaving</dd><br>
<dd>죽어서 세상을 떠남.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of dying and leaving this world.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>하야 [하ː야]</dt><br>
<dd>resignation; stepping down</dd><br>
<dd>관직이나 정치에 관련된 일에서 물러남.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of withdrawing from a goverment post or political matters.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>퇴위 [퇴ː위/퉤ː위]</dt><br>
<dd>1. abdicating the throne</dd><br>
<dd>왕의 자리에서 물러남.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of resigning from the position of king.</dd><br>
<dd>2. resignation; quitting</dd><br>
<dd>관리가 그 직위에서 물러남.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of an official leaving a position.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>퇴사 [퇴ː사/퉤ː사]</dt><br>
<dd>1. leaving work; going home from work</dd><br>
<dd>회사에서 일을 끝내고 집으로 감.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of going home after finishing a day at work.</dd><br>
<dd>2. resignation; quitting a job</dd><br>
<dd>회사를 그만둠.</dd><br>
<dd>To quit one's job at a company.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>퇴거 [퇴ː거/퉤ː거]</dt><br>
<dd>1. leaving; resignation</dd><br>
<dd>있던 자리에서 물러나거나 떠남.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of leaving a place where one has stayed or resigning a job.</dd><br>
<dd>2. moving out; being evicted</dd><br>
<dd>사는 곳을 다른 곳으로 옮김.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of moving one's dwelling place to another place.</dd><br>
<dd>3. secluded life</dd><br>
<dd>세상을 피해 숨어서 지냄.</dd><br>
<dd>One's life led quietly, hiding from the world.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>체념 [체념]</dt><br>
<dd>resignation; surrender</dd><br>
<dd>기대나 희망 등을 버리고 아주 단념함.</dd><br>
<dd>The condition of throwing away or giving up one's expectations, hopes, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사표 [사표]</dt><br>
<dd>resignation; letter of resignation</dd><br>
<dd>직장 등에서 맡고 있던 일 또는 직책을 그만두겠다는 뜻을 적어 내는 글.</dd><br>
<dd>A letter of showing a person's intention to quit his/her job or position at work, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사퇴 [사퇴/사퉤]</dt><br>
<dd>resignation; stepping down</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 직위나 직책을 그만두고 물러남.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of quitting and withdrawing from a certain position and title.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사직서 [사직써]</dt><br>
<dd>letter of resignation; resignation</dd><br>
<dd>맡은 일을 그만두고 물러나게 해 줄 것을 요청하는 서류.</dd><br>
<dd>A letter that states the intention to quit or withdraw from a position.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사직 [사직]</dt><br>
<dd>resignation; stepping down</dd><br>
<dd>맡은 일을 그만두고 물러남.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of quitting and withdrawing from a position.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>사임 [사임]</dt><br>
<dd>resignation; retirement; stepping down</dd><br>
<dd>맡고 있던 일자리를 스스로 그만둠.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of quitting one's position voluntarily.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>